==English==
===Etymology===
German ''[[eigen]]'', own + [[function]]

===Noun===
'''eigenfunction''' (''plural'' '''eigenfunctions''')

#(''mathematics'') A [[function]] &phi; such that, for a particular (differential) linear [[operator]] D, D&phi; = &lambda;&phi; where &lambda; is an [[eigenvalue]] of the operator. 
#(''physics'') In [[quantum mechanics]] you tipically look for eigenfunctions of the [[Hamiltonian]] operator, that are the only [[states]] with a well defined energy; the corresponding eigenvalues are in fact the [[energy levels]] of the system described by such an Hamiltonian. 

